title: Registered Voters in Florida by county by party, Florida
name: Registered Voters in Florida by county by party, Florida
description: The map is based on data from Florida State Election Commission's report on the number of registered voters by precinct and by party as of 31 Dec, 2007, the last date for registering voters for the 2008 primaries and elections. Florida has closed primary, i.e.,  only those registered for a specific party could vote in that party's primary. Since Florida decided to change its primary to an earliers date, DNC has punished Florida by stripping it off all the delgates and all of Democratic candidates have agreed not to campaign in Florida and there no date set for Democratic Primary in Florida. On the Republican side, RNC has punished Florida Republicans by halving the number of delegates for the National Convention.  Republican primay will be held on 29th of January.  Look for other dataset that shows which the Republican and Democratic strongholds acorss the state.
